kernel_variant.question:
Determine, with proof, the minimum value of  

\[
\Phi(r,s,t,u,v)=\Bigl(\tfrac{r}{2}-1\Bigr)^{2}
              +\Bigl(\tfrac{s}{r}-1\Bigr)^{2}
              +\Bigl(\tfrac{t}{s}-1\Bigr)^{2}
              +\Bigl(\tfrac{u}{t}-1\Bigr)^{2}
              +\Bigl(\tfrac{v}{u}-1\Bigr)^{2}
              +\Bigl(\tfrac{64}{v}-1\Bigr)^{2}
\]

over all positive real numbers  

\[
2\le r\le s\le t\le u\le v\le 64 ,\qquad r\,s\,t\,u\,v=2^{15}=32\,768 .
\]

(a)  State the unique quintuple \((r^{\ast},s^{\ast},t^{\ast},u^{\ast},v^{\ast})\)
at which the minimum is attained (four correct decimal places suffice).  

(b)  State the minimum value \(\Phi_{\min }=\Phi(r^{\ast},s^{\ast},t^{\ast},u^{\ast},v^{\ast})\)
(six correct decimal places suffice).

----------------------------------------------------------------

